post_text:
As of this afternoon, there is no state mandate to close schools. We continue to rely on direction from the NJ Department of Health who has advised that schools should remain open unless there is a confirmed case of Coronavirus in our schools. Currently there are no confirmed cases of the virus in our schools or the Manasquan community.

Currently we plan to operate a normal school schedule on Monday, March 16.

The District is continuing its enhanced cleaning and disinfecting protocols.

We are working closely with health authorities, our school physician, and sending district schools to monitor the developing situation. We will continue to communicate any updates via Honeywell Instant Alert and our website manasquanschools.org.

post_text:
Please take note of this important announcement regarding athletics and extracurricular events. More and updated info will be available on manasquanschools.org

At this time, Spring athletic practices and games will continue as scheduled.

In support of the overall public health effort to limit any possible spread of infectious disease, the District is taking the precautionary step of postponing all extra-curricular public activities and events from now through the conclusion of Spring Recess on April 20. This includes concerts, plays, Squan-A-Thon, March Melodies, fashion show, and any other indoor events that will be attended by an audience or large group.

Prior to returning from Spring Recess, we will re-assess the situation and advise the school community of plans moving forward.

post_text: Manasquan High School French students visited Quebec City over the winter break. They visited the world famous Ice Hotel and the Chateau Frontenac (one of the most photographed hotels in the world.) They had action packed days that included activities like dog sledding with Siberian Huskies through the Canadian forest, tubing, and most importantly they were able to practice their French. Madame Thieme, Ms. Cosse, and Mr. Critelli organized the trip and had a great time with the kids.
